Employee:


Requirement Name	User Stories Needed (IDs/titles)	Inputs Needed from Other Sub‑Systems	Downstream Sub‑Systems Depending on This Output	Key BRs (IDs)
1. Employee Self-Service (View, Photo Update, Request Correction)

"US-E2-04: As an employee, I want to view my full employee profile.
US-E2-05: As an employee, I want to update my contact information (e.g., phone number, address).
US-E2-12: As an employee, I want to add a short biography and upload a profile picture.
US-E6-02: As an employee, I want to request corrections of data (e.g., job title or department)."

"Performance Module: Appraisal history (Date, Type, Score).

Organizational Structure: Employee’s assigned Position and Department."	Organizational Structure: If a correction request involves Position/Department, it might trigger an update/review in the Org Structure module. HR Admin/Manager

Roles: All requests (US-E6-02, US-E2-06) feed directly into the HR Manager/Admin’s approval queue.

"BR 2g, 2n, 2o (Address, Phone, Email requirement).
BR 3h (Education Details storage requirement).
BR 16 (Appraisal records saved on profile).
BR 20a (Only authorized roles can modify data)."


2. Department Manager View (Insight & Brief of Team)

"US-E4-01: As a manager, I want to view my team members’ profiles (excluding sensitive info).
US-E4-02: As a manager, I want to see a summary of my team’s job titles, and departments.
US-E6-03: As an HR Admin, I want to be able to search for employees data."

Organizational Structure: Defines the direct supervisor/reporting line by position, which determines the team (direct reports) shown in this view.

Performance Module: Manager’s review of employee profile data supports initiating performance reviews or setting objectives. 	"BR 3d, 3e (Department/Supervisor links required).

BR 10c (Pay Grade/Band definition).
BR 18b (Privacy restrictions applied for Line Managers on sensitive data).
BR 41b (Direct Managers see their team only)."


3. HR Manager/System Admin (Master Data Management & Approval)

"US-EP-04: As an HR admin, I want to edit any part of an employee’s profile.
US-E2-03: As an HR admin, I want to review and approve employee-submitted profile changes before applying them.
US-EP-05: As an HR admin, I want to deactivate an employee’s profile upon termination or resignation.
US-E7-05: As an HR admin, I want to assign roles and access permissions to each employee."

"Onboarding Module: Triggers the creation of the employee profile upon contract signing, setting initial Name, ID, DOB, Date of Hire, and Contract Type.
Leaves Module / Offboarding Module: Actions (Resignation/Termination) automatically set the Current Status field (Active, Suspended, Retired, etc.)."

Payroll & Benefits Module: Updates to Pay Grade, Contract Type, or Status (Active/Suspended/Terminated) directly impact payroll calculations and payment blocking.
Time Management Module: Status updates (e.g., On Leave, Suspended) must sync to time tracking.

"BR 20a (Only authorized roles can create/modify data).
BR 3j (Employee status definition for system access control).
BR 3b, 3f, 3g (Date of Hire, Contract Type requirements).
BR 22 (Trace all editing, changes, and cancellations in a timestamped and trailed manner)."


Action	Actor	Action/Process	Supporting User Stories (US) and Rules (BR)	Outputs & Data Flow



1. View Personal Profile (Self-Service)


Employee

Secure access, authentication, and retrieval of PII (personally identifiable information), employment details (Position, Department, Pay Grade, Appraisals History)	"US-E2-04: As an employee, I want to view my full employee profile.


BR 2a-r: System must record specific personal and job data.
NFR-14: All users shall authenticate via secure login and role-based access control."

Outputs: Display of Employee Profile data (Name, ID, Status, Pay Grade, etc.).

Data Flow: Retrieves Appraisal history from the Performance module.


2. Update Self-Service Data (Immediate Update)

Department Employee

Direct modification and saving of non-critical data points (Profile Picture, Phone, Email, Address).

"US-E2-12: As an employee, I want to upload a profile picture.
US-E2-05: As an employee, I want to update my contact information (e.g., phone number, address).

BR 2n, 2o, 2g: Requirements for Phone, Email, and Address data."

Output: Update Employee Profile Master Data. Data Flow: Triggers Notification N-037 (Profile updated) to employee & HR. All actions traced per BR 22.


3. Submit Request for Correction/Change

Department Employee

Submission of formal request to modify critical, HR-governed data (e.g., Name, National ID, Position, Marital Status).

"US-E6-02: As an employee, I want to request corrections of data (e.g., job title or department).
US-E2-06: As an employee, I want to submit requests to change legal name or marital status.

BR 20a: Only authorized roles can create and/or modify profile data."

Output: Creation of a Pending Change Request record.
Data Flow: Notification N-040 (Profile change request submitted) sent to HR/Manager.



4. View Team Brief (Manager Insight)

Department Manager

Secure access to team list, displaying non-sensitive, summarized profile data filtered by direct reporting line hierarchy.

"US-E4-01: As a manager, I want to view my team members’ profiles (excluding sensitive info).
US-E4-02: As a manager, I want to see a summary of my team’s job titles, and departments.

BR 41b: Direct Managers see their team only.
BR 18b: Privacy restrictions should be applied for Department Managers on sensitive data."

Output: Display of summarized team list (Name, Position, Department, Date of Hire, Status).

Data Flow: Retrieves team structure from Organizational Structure Module.


5. Review and Process Change Request

HR Manager, HR Admin

Review pending change request, validate compliance, and either approve (apply changes to master record) or reject.

"US-E2-03: As an HR admin, I want to review and approve employee-submitted profile changes before applying them.
US-E7-04: As a system admin, I want to configure workflow rules.

BR 36: All changes must be made via workflow approval.
BR 22: Traces any editing, changes, and cancellations in a timestamped and trailed manner."

Output: If Approved: Update Employee Profile Master Data. If change affects hierarchy (Position/Department), trigger update/request in Organizational Structure Module (Dependency 13).
If Rejected: Status of request updated to "Rejected."

Data Flow: Notification N-037 (Profile updated/rejected) sent to employee.


6. Master Data Edit/Management

HR Manager, HR Admin

Direct access to edit/modify any employee profile field (PII, Pay Grade, Status, Hire Date) and configure system rules.

"US-EP-04: As an HR admin, I want to edit any part of an employee’s profile.
US-E7-05: As an HR admin, I want to assign roles and access permissions.

BR 3j: Employee status (Active, On Leave, Suspended, Retired) controls system access.
BR 20a: Only authorized roles can create and/or modify profile data."

Output: Direct update to Employee Profile Master Data.

Data Flow: If Status changes (e.g., Terminated/Suspended), automatic synchronization (BR 20, BR 17) triggers updates to Payroll (to block payment) and Time Management. If Pay Grade changes, automatically updates salary/payroll module (Dependency 40).



